message: Just started experimenting with online shopping with Ebay last month and already Ill never shop with them again. After a lot of research I found a good deal on a wine fridge but when I got it, it was some major damage. I told them I would take a refund if possible or even another fridge...even if I had to pay more (I'm remodeling so most things are new). But the seller said there are no refunds and ebay came right behind them with an email giving me the big middle finger also. So now Im stuck with the wine fridge thats damaged....so had to put it in the corner and try to hide the damage. But the only reason Im even complaining now on FB is because I tried to do it on Ebay (mostly for the seller) and surprisingly I cant find any history on this one particular item I bought. Its mysteriously vanished. Even went to the sellers profile and there was no way to rate that person. So its my fault that I didnt see the no refund policy on this seller but no kind of solution was even entertained....i fell like im easy to work with. So Ill stick with Amazon from now on.

data.message:
These situations can be tough, Chris. The biggest issue here is that when an item isn't as described or, in this case, damaged if a return claim is escalated to us and we're unable to disprove their claim, we would hold the seller to the return shipping cost. If the buyer finds that they are expected to pay this cost, they may be understandably upset. I encourage you to continue to work with your buyer towards a mutual resolution.

In the meantime, you might want to consider insuring your packages in the future. This way, if you have this type of claim you can easily take care of the buyer and recoup costs from the shipper. If you ship using USPS Priority Mail you will automatically have $50 in insurance coverage. If you did that in this case, I recommend that you file a claim and let me know how it goes! ~Brady

data.message:
Hey Jennifer! 

Sorry for any trouble with the item not arriving. We have you covered under these situations with our eBay Money Back Guarantee: http://ebay.to/1zDIMJp for 30 days from the latest estimated delivery. Once this passes though, we're not able to cover you any longer. Unfortunately, this time most likely has passed with the purchase being made in October.

Now, if you paid using PayPal, you may still be covered. PayPal offers additional coverage on situations like this that is for 180 days. I'd reach out to PayPal and look in their Resolution Center if a request can be made. I can't guarantee you are still covered on this either though as you may be at or over 180 days now. ~Cameron
Thank you muchly for getting back to me.. I'll try PayPal.. my last contact I was told he sent another one was March 2nd. So it's still passed your 30 days.. I appreciate the help ^_^

Hi, I purchased a video camera and payed $49 via paypal. I received confirmation of my order and paypal charged my card with the noted amount. This morning I checked the status of my purchase and was surprised to see the following message from Ebay:
 
"We had to remove this listing from the site and you're not required to complete the transaction. If you've already sent payment, the sale should process as normal and you don't have anything to worry about. If you have any questions about delivery, please check tracking or contact your seller. If you run into any trouble along the way eBay is here to help. Please visit the Resolution Centre to help resolve any problems you may encounter."
 
I've immediatelly contacted the seller and received the following reply from him: "My site was hacked, item never existed. Please resolve this directly with ebay."
 
I entered the Ebay resolution center straight away to inform Ebay about the problem, but the site does not have any option for my case to proceed and it keeps asking the item number of the purchase. After entering the item number it says: Looks like you're not buying or selling this item. Choose another item, or look up an item number in My eBay. 
And I cannot go any further after this message. I cannot realize how to get in touch with Ebay and apply for reimbursement.
Please help!
